{
  "texts": [
    "A similar result of 21 problems can be obtained by reducing the search depth from 16 to only two, while keeping the beam size constant at 512.",
    "We evaluated AlphaGeometry and other baselines on a larger test set of 231 geometry problems, curated in ref. 17.",
    "This set covers a wider range of sources outside IMO competitions: textbook examples and exercises, regional olympiads and famous geometry theorems; some are even more complex than typical IMO problems, such as the five circles theorem, Morley's theorem or Sawayama and Thébault's theorem.",
    "The results are reported in Extended Data Fig. 6b.",
    "The overall rankings of different approaches remained the same as in Table 1, with AlphaGeometry solving almost all problems (98.7%)."
  ]
}